PN,43901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FA record #8.5 million paid by water
OL,8,Fcompanies in enforcement action is due
OL,9,Fto be reinvested directly into
OL,10,Frepairing damage to rivers and
OL,11,Fhabitats.
OL,13,FSevern Trent Water paid the most in
OL,14,Fthe Environment Agency crackdown this
OL,15,Ffinancial year. #4,627,424 was
OL,16,Fredirected to local charities
OL,17,Fincluding the Trent Rivers Trust and
OL,18,FGloucestershire Wildlife Trust.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FThese charities will deliver targeted
OL,8,Fimprovements in the affected
OL,9,Fcatchments through measures such as
OL,10,Fhabitat restoration, barrier removal
OL,11,Fand water quality improvements.
OL,13,FElsewhere, #300,000 was paid by Wessex
OL,14,FWater following their pollution of the
OL,15,FRiver Gascoigne. The money will be
OL,16,Fused by the Yeovil Rivers Community
OL,17,FTrust.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FThe total #8.5 million amount paid to
OL,8,Fthe Environment Agency compares to
OL,9,F#5.8 million the year before, a 47%
OL,10,Fincrease, and just under #2 million in
OL,11,Fthe 2023/24 financial year.
OL,13,FThese Enforcement Undertakings are
OL,14,Fvoluntary, legally binding agreements
OL,15,Fbetween the Environment Agency and
OL,16,Fcompanies that have breached
OL,17,Fenvironmental rules. They require the
OL,18,Fcompany to take steps to prevent
OL,19,Frepetition of the offending and to put
OL,20,Fright the damage it has caused.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FOften this will involve a payment to a
OL,8,Fthird-party wildlife trust or
OL,9,Fenvironmental charity, without
OL,10,Frequiring court proceedings.
OL,11,FEnforcement Undertakings are not
OL,12,Ffunded by customer bills.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FA Severn Trent spokesperson said: "Our
OL,8,Ffocus is always on preventing
OL,9,Fpollutions before they happen, but
OL,10,Fwhen things do go wrong, we act
OL,11,Fquickly, take ownership and put things
OL,12,Fright. This funding supports
OL,13,Forganisations like the Rivers Trust to
OL,14,Fmake a difference, while we continue
OL,15,Fto invest billions in our network to
OL,16,Fbuild resilience for the long term."
OL,26,@oD@cOUxD@dO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FMeanwhile, Wessex Water said: "There
OL,8,Fwere no serious pollutions on the
OL,9,FWessex Water sewer network last year
OL,10,Fbut we recognise that incidents such
OL,11,Fas that near Milborne Port, which
OL,12,Fdates back to 2022 and resulted in the
OL,13,FEnforcement Undertaking, are never
OL,14,Facceptable.
OL,26,@oD@_OU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,F"Reducing pollutions will always be a
OL,8,Ftop priority for us, which is why
OL,9,Fwe've invested in AI technology on our
OL,10,Fnetwork to detect where potential
OL,11,Fissues might occur ` meaning we can
OL,12,Fact faster to minimise any
OL,13,Fenvironmental impact.
OL,15,F"The next four years will see more
OL,16,Fthan #3.6 billion of new investment in
OL,17,Fprojects across the region to improve
OL,18,Four assets and protect the
OL,19,Fenvironment."
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FAccording to the Environment Agency,
OL,8,Fthis year's record figures follow a
OL,9,Fmajor increase in enforcement
OL,10,Factivity, including a record 10,000
OL,11,Finspections of water company sites and
OL,12,Fa significant rise in criminal
OL,13,Finvestigations.
OL,15,FIt said that "more staff, better data,
OL,16,Fand increased powers" mean the
OL,17,Fregulator can "act faster when
OL,18,Fbreaches occur and enable more
OL,19,Ftargeted regulatory action".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1776334011
OL,3,CRecord #8.5 million paid by water
OL,4,Ccompanies in enforcement action this
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FWater Minister Emma Hardy said: "Water
OL,8,Fcompanies must be held to account when
OL,9,Fthey break the law."
OL,11,FShe added: "It comes alongside other
OL,12,Fgovernment action to clean up our
OL,13,Frivers, lakes and seas. We've already
OL,14,Fbanned unfair bonuses and introduced
OL,15,Flandmark legislation to hold water
OL,16,Fcompanies to account, and our long-
OL,17,Fterm reforms will mean there is a new,
OL,18,Fsingle regulator focused on preventing
OL,19,Fproblems before they occur."
OL,26,@oD@aOUsD@LOU{D@\O]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
